# Description

This small plugin enables you to publish (and update, to some extent) posts on www.blogger.com right inside vim! I have tried a few other plugins and didn't feel very happy, so decided to roll my own.

# Requirements

* Operating system: tested on Mac OSX mavericks and Ubuntu 14.04
* Tested in Vim 7.4, but should also work on 7.3
* Python support is required, check `echo has('python')` in vim
* A few python packages, this shell command should do it:

<pre>
pip install gdata Beautifulsoup4 lxml markdown2 html5lib
</pre>


# Installation

Put this line in your `~/.vimrc`

    Plugin 'kindlychung/vimBlogger'

then open up vim and do `:PluginInstall`.

# Setup

You need to put you gmail account and password in the config file
`~/.vimbloggerrc`, make sure itâ€™s kept safe. The format is simple:

        jane@eyre.com
        jane'sBeautifulPassWord
        84073810478078

The third line is your blog id, you can get it like in the picture

# Usage

Only two functions are provided:

-   `Bnew`: create a new post
-   `Bpost:` publish the current buffer as a post, or update it if itâ€™s
    already publilshed

Now letâ€™s try it, fire up vim and do `Bnew`, you will see something like
this:

    <!-- ##################################
            Title of your cool blog post
            (plain text)
         ################################## -->
    <posttitle>
    sample title
    </posttitle>

    <!-- ##################################
            Content of your cool blog post
            (html format)
         ################################## -->
    <content>
    <p>
    sample content
    </p>
    </content>

    <!-- ########################################################################
            Labels, one per line, starts with @@, c-x c-k for autocompletion
         ######################################################################## -->
    <labels>
    @@sample_label1
    @@sample_label2
    </labels>

Just fill the title and content in, put your labels behind those @@
signs and do `Bpost`, and you are done! For the content part, markdown
format is used. html can still be used, python-markdown2 will just
ignore it (skip translation).

And if you save the buffer, the plugin will publish the post for you
automatically.

Well, I told you, itâ€™s simple stuff. :-)

# Other configurations

-   `~/.vimblogger_labels` is used to store your labels, and also as a
    dictionary for autocompletion. If you want you can edit the file
    manually, one keyword per line. Please use only letters, numbers and
    underscores for keywords (labels in blogger terms). You can also
    just leave it alone, the plugin will accumulate your labels for you
    over time.
-   `~/.vimblogger_words` is used as a dictionary file for looking up
    (ctrl-x ctrl-k) for everything except labels. You can leave it alone
    if you donâ€™t need such a functionality. If you want it, on Linux and
    Mac OSX, you can do `cp /usr/share/dict/words ~/.vimblogger_words`

* Added an `autocmd` for publishing post before writing file

line, i.e. if line begins with @@, use ~/.vimblogger_labels, otherwise use
~/.vimblogger_words
* Check ~/.vimblogger_words at startup, if non-existent, create an empty file with that name
